providers.headline: Conversational, engaging, fun, heart-full, wise, comforting, warm, knowledgeable, upscale, many dialects and comic characters
providers.summary: My voice qualities are: warm and engaging for narration, exceptionally fun and dynamic for e-Learning, soothing and empathetic for pharma, and upscale, very smart, and smooth for professional presentations.  I have outstandingly fun characters in my wheelhouse as well!

providers.additional_details:
My happy corporate clients include but are not limited to: Hood Sour Cream, Pledge, Crisco, Lysol, Pampers, J&J Disposable Diapers, Kleenex, Oxydol, Deerpark Water, Jello, Best Stores etc.
BA in Drama from UC Berkeley (Dean's list), graduate level work in clinical psychology Pepperdine University
2 years full time acting training at The American Conservatory Theater in S.F. (won best actress in yearly national theater school competition)
2 years full time acting training in the Sanford Meisner method in NYC
2 years full time voice over training at Voicetrax, voice-over academy in Sausalito, Ca. 
Additional training with Thom Pinto, J Michael Collins, Peter Dunne & Brian Sommer
Improvisation at Bay Area Theater Sports, Rachel Hamilton
3 years singing training
Highest quality professionally designed voice studio with immaculate acoustic control. Primary microphone is an ADK TC/TT tube condenser microphone, Focusrite Scarlett 2i2 second generation, and Beyerdynamic DT 770 Studio headphones.
I am a master at taking direction! Why? I listen really well, am extremely smart, and flexible. I have a lot of talent for variety.
providers.description: I excel at eLearning, explainer and corporate narration. You will get exactly what you want based on my excellent ability to take direction. I am a master at it!
